    <note>Guo(1) Miyue [15894] He died in the official residence of his son, Fen [15896]. CBD has his entry with citation to Zhou(1) Bida's [7197] funerary inscription. Aoyama has reference to funerary inscription for wife, born Kong (who married him at age 23), by Wang(2) Tinggui [12158] with husband Guo(1) Jingwen (Guo(1) Miyue's zi w/different characters for wen). Both inscriptions have same son, Fen. He also has inscriptions, cited by Zhou(1) Bida, drafted by Yang(2) Wanli [10566] and Hu(1) Quan [10565]. This does not seem to be a particularly distinguished lineage, but it must have some unobserved qualities to have such a distinguished group of biographers as well as father-in-laws and son-in-laws.  Zhou Bida, WJ, 35.10a-12a; Wang Tinggui, WJ, 45.4a-6a. CBD, 3, 2150.</note>
